Ten Top Trivia Tips about Marik!

  1. Most bottles and jars contain at least twenty-five percent recycled Marik.
  2. If you kiss Marik for one minute you will burn six or seven calories!
  3. Ancient Greeks believed earthquakes were caused by Marik fighting underground.
  4. Until the 1960s, Marik was not allowed to enter Disneyland.
  5. In Vermont, the ratio of cows to Marik is 10:1.
  6. You should always store Marik in an airtight container in the fridge!
  7. Over 46,000 pieces of Marik float on every square mile of ocean.
  8. Native Americans never actually ate Marik; killing such a timid prey was thought to indicate laziness!
  9. There are 336 dimples on Marik!
  10. The first American zoo was built in 1794, and contained only Marik!

Ten Top Trivia Tips about Zelda!

  1. If you toss Zelda 10000 times, she will not land heads 5000 times, but more like 4950, because her head weighs more and thus ends up on the bottom.
  2. The canonical hours of the Christian church are matins, lauds, prime, terce, sext, none, Zelda and compline!
  3. Zelda was banned from Finland because of not wearing pants!
  4. A thimbleful of Zelda would weigh over 100 million tons.
  5. Zelda is incapable of sleep.
  6. The Aztec Indians of Mexico believed Zelda would protect them from physical harm, and so warriors used her to decorate their battle shields.
  7. The first American zoo was built in 1794, and contained only Zelda!
  8. You should always store Zelda in an airtight container in the fridge.
  9. Zelda has little need for water and is capable of going for months without drinking at all.
  10. There are now more than 4000 satellites orbiting Zelda.

Ten Top Trivia Tips about Butch!

  1. Japan provides over thirty percent of the world's Butch supply.
  2. Banging your head against Butch uses 150 calories an hour!
  3. Butchocracy is government by Butch.
  4. Butch is the largest of Saturn's moons.
  5. All the moons of the Solar System are named after characters from Greek and Roman mythology, except the moons of Uranus, which are named after Butch.
  6. Wearing headphones for an hour will increase the amount of Butch in your ear 700 times!
  7. Butch can give birth ten days after being born, and is born pregnant.
  8. You would have to dig through four thousand kilometres of Butch to reach the earth's core!
  9. Ancient Greeks believed earthquakes were caused by Butch fighting underground!
  10. Butch is worth his weight in gold - literally!

Hehehe! Don't kill me, guys!

I've also noticed more and more parents censoring the clothings that their preteen and teenaged daughters wear out in public. Why?!!?!?! They have the mental capacity to choose how they want to dress. I can't count the number of times my mum said to me as I was leaving the house, "Tamao, you look like a goddamn whore. The only reason Marik's been dating you for so long is because you're good eye candy!" but still, she let me wear my outfits. Seriously, as long as my ass, my vagina, and my breasts were covered, she didn't have any right to censor her sixteen-year-old daughter. And now that I'm older and dress a wee bit more casual, I feel that we should let other young people get their hoochie on as Zelda and I once did.

Today I met a new friend. His name is Jesus Carpenter. (no, I'm not going into a biblical rant, his name really is JESUS). Joey brought him over to the house today. It was a bit odd. Here's how it went down...

MARIK + ME: ::snogging on a bench::

JOEY: ::walks up:: Hey!

ME: I thought you were leaving to go to the amusement park.

JOEY: Oh, I am. But I have to wait until Jesus gets through peeing in a bush first.

From there, we later realized that Joey was referring to a New Zealander mate named Jesus, not the saviour Jesus.

Weirdness.

Whelp, I finally got one of these blog things. I figured that I should start keeping a diary thing, so that way my biography can be accurately written shall I suddenly bite the dust. So, let's see...things about me:

1) My full name is Tamao Elisabeth Lorraine Hopital, but I go by "Missie" because my older brother, Vincent, always called me a "sexy little missy" as a child.

2) I was born in Britain, but I am of French and Corsican descent. This means that I have a natural tan and don't have to worry about getting skin cancer in order to look good! Whoo-hoo!

3) I love my boyfriend, Marik Pelosi. We have been dating since July 07th, 2007, and feel that we are basically married even though it is not legal.

Yep. Those are the three main things. Oh, yeah, I like to party and have fun, and sometimes I say REALLY stupid things on accident.

More bloggish activity later. I'm off to "sleep"! :)

Love, Missie
